<item>
            <title>[NET-695] Apply SocketClient timeout after connection but before SSL negotiation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-695</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Apply SocketClient timeout after connection but before SSL negotiation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that this is is a different timeout from the connect timeout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This applies to the following &lt;tt&gt;SocketClient&lt;/tt&gt; subclasses:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;FTPSClient&lt;/tt&gt;; see also &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-net/pull/70&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-net/pull/70&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;POP3SClient&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SMTPSClient&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
